### What problem does this feature solve?
We know that we can not attempt to access user defined globals in template expressions. 
As a C# WPF user, I love Vue.js, and I use Vue.js and TypeScirpt to build my projects at work.
I hope that Vue.js support some syntax just like 'xmlns' in xaml.
Maybe this will come true some day in the future.

### What does the proposed API look like?
# issue

```typescript
// MyEnums.ts
export enum Shape {
  Rectangle = 'rectangle',
  Ellipse = 'ellipse ',
  Triangle = 'triangle ',
  Hexagon = 'hexagon ',
}

export enum Size {
  Small = 'small',
  Medium = 'medium ',
  Large = 'large ',
}
```

```typescript
// MyClass.ts
export default class MyClass {
  static get currentTime(): Date {
    return new Date();
  }
}
```

```html
<!-- MyComponent.vue -->
<template>
  <div class="my-component"
       :class="classes">
    <slot></slot>
  </div>
</template>

<script lang="ts">
import { Component, Vue, Prop } from 'vue-property-decorator';
import { Shape, Size } from './MyEnums';

@Component
export default class MyComponent extends Vue {
  @Prop() shape: Shape;
  @Prop() size: Size;

  get classes(): Array<any> {
    return [`shape-${this.shape}`, `size-${this.size}`];
  }
}
</script>
```

```html
<!-- App.vue -->
<template v-import="import { Shape, Size } from './MyEnums'"
          v-import="import MyClass from './MyClass'">
  <div class="app">
    <p>curent time: {{MyClass.currentTime}}</p>
    <my-component :shap="Shape.Ellipse"
                  :size="Size.Medium"></my-component>
  </div>
</template>

<script lang="ts">
import { Component, Vue } from 'vue-property-decorator';
import MyComponent from './MyComponent.vue';

@Component
export default class App extends Vue {}
</script>
```

